<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have a finger in something • pull one’s finger out</xh5><p> <i>have a finger in something</i>—(also: have a hand in something) be involved in smth.; play a role in smth.: Possibly the Russians might have <u>had a finger in</u> this. The cold war was raging at that time.</p><p> <i>pull one’s finger out</i>—(sl.) start working more efficiently <i>(also: get one’s finger out):</i> We’re still waiting for the reviewer to <u>pull his finger out</u> and deliver. Serves us right for recruiting literary talent in a bar.</p> </entry>
